[3] Prevention & suspect cases

Guinea: riot in Nzerekore over disinfectant
-----------------------------------
29 Aug 2014: Residents of Guinea's 2nd-biggest city have rioted after the market was sprayed with disinfectant in a bid to halt the spread of the ebolavirus.... Local traders were apparently not warned and held a protest march to the city's hospital, which was attacked. Police responded by firing tear gas and a 24-hour curfew was imposed. Local Red Cross workers had to flee to a military base.... Youssouf Traore, president of the Guinean Red Cross, said the rioters had fired guns. "A rumour, which was totally false, spread that we had sprayed the market in order to transmit the virus to locals," he said ... [more]
http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-28984259

Nigeria: Port Harcourt
----------------------
Sister of dead EVD doctor escapes from Port Harcourt as 200 are quarantined
29 Aug 2014: SaharaReporters has learned that a sister of a Port Harcourt-based medical doctor, who recently died from the ebolavirus, fled to Abia State to avoid being quarantined with others who came into contact with the late doctor. However, one of her siblings, who is also a doctor, forced her to return to the quarantine center in Port Harcourt, the capital of Rivers State ... [more]
http://saharareporters.com/2014/08/29/sister-dead-ebola-doctor-escapes-port-harcourt-200-are-quarantined-rivers-state

Nigeria: EVD Ministry of Health Release
---------------------------------------
29 Aug 2014: "If you visited Samstel Clinic, Rumuokoro, Port Harcourt, within the last few weeks, you are kindly urged to report to the Rivers State Health Ministry! Please search yourself and if this concerns you, please go and get tested immediately. If you were in this hospital but have left Port Harcourt, please look for where to give yourself up. Everything is being done to curb the spread. Please do your little part to help. Do not hide family members who you think might be infected." 217 people have so far been quarantined in Port Harcourt.
http://lindaikeji.blogspot.co.uk/2014/08/ebola-rivers-state-min-of-health-ask.html

Belgium
-------
EVD suspected cases in Belgium ex Guinea
29 Aug 2014: Guinean in quarantine in Ostend had malaria not EVD; MSF collaborator in quarantine in Brussels hospital suspected of contamination with EVD ... [more]
http://www.lesoir.be/639168/article/actualite/sciences-et-sante/2014-08-29/ebola-en-belgique-collaborateur-msf-est-un-premier-cas-suspect [in French]

Canada
------
Canadian hospital staffers get EVD workshops
28 Aug 2014: (Globe & Mail) While federal public health authorities have assured Canadians that there is very little risk of an EVD outbreak, hospitals across the country are training staff and reinforcing protocols should an infected patient walk through their doors ... [more]
http://www.theglobeandmail.com/life/health-and-fitness/health/canadian-hospital-staffers-get-ebola-workshops/article20262430

Guinea-Bissau: 8 people quarantined
-----------------------------------
28 Aug 2014: 8 people from Guinea Conakry are quarantined at the Regional Hospital of Gabu in eastern Guinea-Bissau. These individuals have entered the country secretly. EVD has not yet come to Guinea-Bissau but authorities have been taking a series of preventive measures.
http://www.portugues.rfi.fr/africa/20140828-oito-pessoas-em-quarentena-no-leste-da-guine-bissau [in Portuguese]

Indonesia: hajj pilgrims
------------------------
29 Aug 2014: Around 170 000 Indonesians are set to fly to Saudi Arabia for the annual haj pilgrim in the coming weeks, but few are aware of the lurking danger of the ebolavirus, following the deaths of at least 1500 people in western Africa over the past 6 months. While Indonesia is fully geared up to handle the virus with isolation facilities established in around 100 hospitals nationwide, the country's preventive measures against the virus have been questioned. Indonesian Haj and Umrah Tour and Travel Union (Kesthuri) and Nahdlatul Ulama's Haj and the Umrah Counselors Association (Asbihu-NU) said recently that they had received no information from the health authorities on precautionary measures against the virus.... The 1st batch of Indonesia's haj pilgrims is slated to depart for Saudi Arabia on 1 Sep 2014, and will return in the 1st week of October.
http://m.thejakartapost.com/news/2014/08/29/danger-ebola-haj-pilgrims-kept-dark.html

USA, UK: West African student screening
--------------------------
EVD in mind, US and UK colleges screen some students
29 Aug 2014: (AP) US universities count 9728 active students from Nigeria, 204 from Liberia, 169 from Sierra Leone and 95 students from Guinea, according to the USA federal government. College students from West Africa may be subject to extra health checks when they arrive to study in the USA, as administrators try to insulate campuses from the worst EVD outbreak in history.

Universities in the United Kingdom also are on alert with the expected arrival of thousands of Nigerian students there. Universities UK, which represents universities, has circulated guidance from Public Health England advising administrators on how to recognize and react to possible cases.
http://www.miamiherald.com/2014/08/29/4315805/ebola-in-mind-us-colleges-screen.html

Zimbabwe: 21-Day Quarantine for EVD Suspects
--------------------------------------------
29 Aug 2014: (AllAfrica) People who travel to Zimbabwe from countries that have been affected by the ebolavirus will be quarantined for 21 days, while prophets who claim to cure HIV and Aids, diabetes and cancer risk being arrested for urging patients to stop taking medication, the Senate heard yesterday [28 Aug 2014].
http://allafrica.com/stories/201408290459.html

